A Go library for SVG generation

Supported SVG elements:
  circle, ellipse, polygon, polyline, rect (including roundrects), arc,
  cubic and quadratic bezier paths, line, image, use, text
  
The library generates SVG to standard output
  
See svgobj.[svg|png|pdf] for a graphical view of the function calls


Usage: (where $GC and $GL are the Go compiler and linker for your targer architecture)

  $ $GC svg.go  # compile the library
  $ $GC svgobj.go && $GL -o svgobj svgobj.6  # compile a client program
  $ ./svgobj    # run the client program
  
This package includes:

svg.go       Library
svgobj.go    Creates a SVG representation of the API
vismem.go    Visualize data from files
randcomp.go  Compare random number generators
planets.go   Show the scale of the Solar system
rl.go        Random lines (port of a Processing demo)
imfade.go    Show image fading
images/*     Images used by the client programs

You may view the SVG output directly using a browser that supports SVG (Chrome and Safari tested), 
or any other SVG user-agent such Batik Squiggle


  
